TROY OUNCE was quick to the lead, set a pressured pace, kicked clear from upper stretch when pushed along, but was reeled in past the furlong mark and no match for BOURBON DELIGHT late. BEHAVIN MYSELF broke outward, chased midfield through the first turn, advanced to join outside of DEVIL'S RULE to stalk the leading pair two wide down the backstretch, tracked the leading pair in the three path around the far turn, was driven in upper stretch, and chased on while proving no match for the leading pair in the lane. DEVIL'S RULE tracked the leading pair, raced very keenly around the first turn and down the back straight, was pushed along in the four to five path on the far turn, went to a drive near the quarter, and lacked the needed rally in the lane. KRAMDEN broke inward, settled near the rear, continued toward the rear in the two path on the far turn, and offered no rally. GAGOOTS was bumped between BEHAVIN MYSELF and KRAMDEN in the opening strides, settled at the rear, trailed in the four path on the far turn while driven, and had no response.
